(45, 'MeSH', 'http://www.library.arizona.edu', '', '<p><img class="heading" src="tutorials/view_heading_image/chapter/Activity%20-%20Determining%20MeSH%20Terms%20for%20an%20Article" alt="" /><span lang="en-US">\r\n<div style="margin: 0pt;"><span lang="en-US"><span style="font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">(Try it: <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21090937" target="site-frame">http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21090937</a>)</span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: 11pt;"><span style="font-family: Times New Roman,serif; font-size: small;"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">NLM  indexers examine articles and assign the most specific MeSH heading(s)  that appropriately describes the concept(s) discussed. The indexer will assign as many MeSH  headings as appropriate to cover the topics of the article (generally 5  to 15). </span></span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">The MeSH terms that reflect the major points of the article are marked with an asterisk (*).</span></span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">Step 1. <span style="text-decoration: line-through;">Select the article of interest by clicking on the title.</span> By default when you click on the title of an article of interest from your results, it will display in Abstract view. </span></span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">&nbsp;</span></span><span lang="en-US"><span style="font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: 11pt;"><img class="heading" src="tutorials/view_heading_image/step/" alt="" /></span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">(Try it: <a href="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21090937" target="site-frame">http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21090937</a>) </span></span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div style="margin: 0pt;"><span style="font-family: Calibri,sans-serif; font-size: x-small;"><span style="font-size: 11pt;">Step  2. Activate the drop-down menu next to Display Settings on the top left  and select MEDLINE. Then click the Apply button. Review all the entries  with the MH tag. </span></span></div>\r\n</span></p>', 1, NULL, 1, 1, 1, 'Elizabeth Kline', 'klinee@u.library.arizona.edu', '', 0, NULL, NULL, 'Submit', NULL, 1, '2010-11-30 15:47:37', '2010-11-30 15:52:16', 0),
